<HEADLINE> Wizards Fire Coach Bickerstaff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Bernie Bickerstaff was fired as coach of the  
Washington Wizards today after the team dropped to a 13-19 record 
in the shortened season. 
</P>
<P>
	Assistant Jim Brovelli was appointed interim head coach.  
</P>
<P>
	``I felt this team wasn't moving in the direction that we  
anticipated,'' general manager Wes Unseld said. ``This is one of 
the toughest decisions that I've had to make, but it was my feeling 
that a change was necessary at this time.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Wizards, who lost 90-79 to Miami on Sunday, are in fifth  
place in the Atlantic Division. 
