<HEADLINE> Ex-Air Canada Exec To World Airways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HERNDON, Va. (AP) -- Hollis L. Harris, president and chairman of  
Air Canada since January 1993, has been named to the same position 
at charter carrier World Airways Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	Harris will succeed Russell L. Ray Jr. on May 1, World Airways  
announced Monday. Ray is retiring but will continue as a director 
of the company. 
</P>
<P>
	Before joining Air Canada, Harris was chairman of Air Eagle  
Holdings, an aviation consulting firm he founded with four 
partners. He previously served as president of Continental Airlines 
and Delta Airlines. 
</P>
<P>
	World Airways is a charter carrier operating a fleet of 12  
widebody MD-11 and DC-10-30 aircraft. The company offered a limited 
number of regular passenger flights earlier this decade but 
suspended them in 1996 because they proved unprofitable. 

</P>
</TEXT>
