</P>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- After yesterday's season opener in Mexico,  
the major league baseball year is launched today in the United 
States. Among the biggest pitching matchups is Arizona's Randy 
Johnson and his $52 million contract facing baseball's first $100 
million man, Kevin Brown of the Los Angeles Dodgers. Other meetings 
topping the schedule include the defending World Champion Yankees, 
with Roger Clemens making his debut, taking on the Oakland 
Athletics. 

</P>
