skies over Yugoslavia, hit bridges, fuel depots and army barracks, 
taking aim at Serb forces accused of pushing ethnic Albanians out 
of Kosovo. In Belgrade, air raid sirens sounded on the 13th 
straight night of NATO bombardments vs. Serbian positions. Yugoslav 
officials said five people were killed and at least 30 injured in 
an attack on a southern Serb town of Aleksinac. That report 
couldn't confirmed independently but an Associated Press 
photographer at the scene saw two victims. State-run Serbian TV 
showed what looked like a residential area that was destroyed. 

