today to racketeering, bribery, extortion and other charges. He did 
so in exchange for a prison term of up to seven years. Gotti also 
was fined $1 million and must forfeit $1 million in cash and 
property that prosecutors say are proceeds from his criminal 
ventures. Jury selection was to begin tomorrow in his federal 
trial. If convicted, Gotti could have been sentenced to 20 years in 
prison. He was charged with taking part in a criminal enterprise 
known as the Gambino family, and extortion, robbery, loansharking, 
gambling and bribery. 

