avoided a possible death sentence with his plea. He was sentenced 
to two consecutive life terms. Authorities said Henderson and Aaron 
McKinney posed as homosexuals and lured Shepard out of a bar last 
October, kidnapped and pistol-whipped him and left him tied to a 
fence. 

