<DOCNO> APW19990405.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-05 10:35:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> J.C. Penney To Start Teen Magazine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PLANO, Texas (AP) -- J.C. Penney plans to publish a new magazine  
for teen-agers and distribute it for free in its stores. 
</P>
<P>
	J.C. Penney said the quarterly magazine, tentatively called  
``Noise,'' would start with a circulation of 3.5 million. The first 
issue is due in July. The retailer has hired Redwood CMP to produce 
the magazine. 
</P>
<P>
	The first issue will be 84 pages and include 35 percent  
advertising, which will likely consist of J.C. Penney ads and those 
of the retailer's vendors. 
</P>
<P>
	The retailer said it will give ``Noise'' away at its 1,150  
stores across the country and consider a direct mail distribution 
in the future. 
</P>
<P>
	``We see this magazine as a vehicle to create a strong, personal  
relationship with a very important customer -- teen-agers,'' said 
Gale Duff-Bloom, president of J.C. Penney Marketing and 
Communications. 
</P>
<P>
	The full-color magazine will focus on the latest teen beauty and  
fashion styles and trends as well as features on sports and music. 
</P>
<P>
	J.C. Penney would not disclose how much the magazine will cost  
to launch. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
