<HEADLINE> Costner Plays in Big League Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- ``Field of Dreams'' star Kevin Costner  
realized one of his biggest dreams -- playing in a big league 
baseball game. 
</P>
<P>
	He also realized one of his biggest fears -- making an error  
Sunday to lose the game. 
</P>
<P>
	Costner dropped a ball in the sixth inning, allowing the scoring  
run as the Anaheim Angels defeated his alma mater, Cal State 
Fullerton, 2-1 in the Angels' exhibition finale. 
</P>
<P>
	Costner was hitless in three times at bat. But he made two tough  
plays at shortstop, and even pitched two-thirds of an inning, 
striking out rookie Jeb Daugherty and retiring Angels manager Terry 
Collins on a ground ball in the eighth. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a really great day, but it would have been better  
without the error,'' Costner, 44, said. ``I felt really bad about 
making us lose the game. I just missed it in front of everybody. I 
really wanted to win.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Still, Angels pitcher Chuck Finley liked what he saw from  
Costner. 
</P>
<P>
	``He actually handled himself pretty well out there,'' Finley  
said. ``You can tell he's a good athlete. He made a couple plays 
that impressed me, especially on that backhander.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Costner has starred in baseball movies as ``Field of Dreams''  
and ``Bull Durham,'' in which he performed his own baseball stunts. 
He recently played a pitcher in the upcoming ``For The Love of The 
Game.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
