San Antonio was approved last month by shareholders of both 
companies. 
</P>
<P>
	The $4.4 billion deal will form the nation's second-largest  
radio station operating company, with 450 radio stations in 101 
U.S. markets, plus 20 television stations and outdoor advertising 
businesses in 25 countries. 

