<HEADLINE> Sports Editor John Bibb Dies at 72 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- John Bibb, a retired sports editor for  
The Tennessean, is dead after a long illness. He was 72. 
</P>
<P>
	Bibb, a member of the Tennessee Sports Hall of Fame and a  
two-time president of the Golf Writers Association of America, died 
Sunday at St. Thomas Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	Bibb was known for his witty columns.  
</P>
<P>
	``Sports writers, athletes and coaches from all over the nation  
will remember John as a great sports editor and writer,'' said John 
Seigenthaler, chairman emeritus of The Tennessean. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was that, of course. But more than anything else he was a  
great human being, a great husband and a father, a great mentor and 
to me a great friend.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bibb also worked as a sports commentator on WSM's ``Waking  
Crew'' program. He later joined the ``Roundtable'' program, where 
he offered views on politics and other topics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
