<DOCNO> APW19990405.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-05 13:35:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 5 Supreme Court Justices Are Absent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The ritual that begins each Supreme Court  
session -- the marshal's command of ``Oyez, oyez, oyez,'' the 
courtroom crowd rising to its feet, the justices appearing from 
behind scarlet curtains to take the bench -- was missing something 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Or rather, it was missing someone. Actually, five someones.  
</P>
<P>
	Only four of the court's nine members showed up for the brief  
session in which the court released orders and announced decisions. 
</P>
<P>
	Chief Justice William H. Rehnquist ran the show as usual, but  
only Justices Sandra Day O'Connor, Ruth Bader Ginsburg and Stephen 
G. Breyer flanked him. The other five chairs were empty. 
</P>
<P>
	The missing: Justices John Paul Stevens, Antonin Scalia, Anthony  
M. Kennedy, David H. Souter and Clarence Thomas. 
</P>
<P>
	Asked about the absenteeism, court spokesman Ed Turner refused  
to comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
