<HEADLINE> Thunderstorm Damages Wichita Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- A thunderstorm caused extensive damage  
today at a school and a nearby shopping area. No serious injuries 
were reported. 
</P>
<P>
	There was no immediate confirmation whether the storm included a  
tornado, the National Weather Service said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Something went through there with gusto,'' said Conrad Rohr, a  
Wichita resident who saw some of the damage. 
</P>
<P>
	Three portable classrooms in trailers at Jefferson Elementary  
School were destroyed, windows were broken in the main school 
building and teachers' cars were overturned, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Eighteen children eating breakfast in the school cafeteria were  
moved to a heavily bricked section for protection when warning 
sirens blared. The children were unhurt. 
</P>
<P>
	``Can you imagine if it were school time?'' said Jan Ostenberg,  
a fifth-grade teacher. 
</P>
<P>
	About two blocks away, a strip mall was heavily damaged.  
</P>
<P>
	Police also reported gas leaks, downed power lines and snapped  
trees. A vehicle was trapped by high water but no one's life was in 
danger, Deputy Chief Terri Moses said. 
</P>
<P>
	Wind topping 65 mph was reported at McConnell Air Force Base.  
</P>
<P>
	A tornado on Saturday killed six people at Benton, La.  
</P>
<P>
	And late Sunday, a tornado damaged more than a dozen homes in  
the East Texas town of Maydelle. No serious injuries were reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
