<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Higher; Dow Up 129.04 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Technology issues led the stock market sharply  
higher Monday amid signs that the economy's fast rate of growth may 
be moderating. 
</P>
<P>
	At noon on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was up  
129.04 at 9,961.55. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq composite index was up 31.97 at 2,493.37, just shy of  
its record close of 2,510.09 reached Feb. 1. The technology-laden 
index had traded as high as 2,539.40 earlier in the session. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were also higher.  
</P>
<P>
	On Friday, the Labor Department reported 46,000 new jobs were  
created in February, the smallest increase in three years. The news 
calmed investor fears that the economy was growing too fast and 
that the Federal Reserve might raise interest rates to slow it 
down. The report, issued when the market was closed in observance 
of Good Friday, also said the unemployment rate fell to a 29-year 
low of 4.2 percent as wages rose less than expected. 
</P>
<P>
	Technology stocks once again set the tone for the session.  
</P>
<P>
	Among Dow stocks, IBM was up 4 3/8 to 181 3/8 and Hewlett-Packard rose  
3 1/4 to 71 1/8. 
</P>
<P>
	On the Nasdaq market, Yahoo! shot up 24 to 203 3/4 as traders  
anticipated a strong earnings report from the Internet company on 
Wednesday. Computer maker Dell was up 2 3/8 at 43 9/16, Sun 
Microsystems gained 3 7/16 to 129 5/8, and Microsoft was up 2 1/16 at 
94 3/4. 
</P>
<P>
	The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 17.82 at 1,311.54.  
</P>
<P>
	Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-3 margin on the  
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 405.9 million shares, 
up from Thursday's 332.92 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was up 6.20 at 611.19, and the American  
Stock Exchange composite index was up 5.61 at 716.91. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
