<HEADLINE> Women's World Cup Soccer Is Popular </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- More than 300,000 tickets have been sold for  
this summer's Women's World Cup, tournament organizers said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The figure, including 40,000 tickets for the opening  
doubleheader at Giants Stadium in East Rutherford, M.J., June 19, 
is almost triple the 112,000 seats sold for the last tournament in 
Sweden in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials also said the U.S. team would set up training camp at  
the Pingry School in Bernards Township, N.J., June 12, one week 
before it begins the tournament against Denmark. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
