<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Knoxville, Tenn., Gets Hockey Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KNOXVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Minor league hockey is back in  
Knoxville. 
</P>
<P>
	Andrew Wilhelm said Monday he was moving his United Hockey  
League franchise from Madison, Wis., to Knoxville for next season. 
</P>
<P>
	The 4-year-old franchise will have many of the same players as  
the old Madison Monsters, but it will get a new name that will be 
picked by fans. 
</P>
<P>
	Knoxville has been without a minor league hockey team since the  
Cherokees moved to South Carolina after the 1997 season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
